NAME
    gcloud alpha container binauthz authorities set-iam-policy - set the IAM
        policy for an authority

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud alpha container binauthz authorities set-iam-policy AUTHORITY_NAME
        POLICY_FILE [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (ALPHA) See https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/managing-policies for details
    of the policy file format and contents.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     AUTHORITY_NAME
        The name of the authority whose IAM policy will be updated.

     POLICY_FILE
        The JSON or YAML file containing the IAM policy.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --configuration,
    --flatten, --format, --help, --log-http, --project, --quiet, --trace-token,
    --user-output-enabled, --verbosity. Run $ gcloud help for details.

EXAMPLES
    The following command will read an IAM policy defined in a JSON file
    'iam_policy.json' and set it for the authority my_authority:

        $ gcloud alpha container binauthz authorities set-iam-policy \
            my_authority iam_policy.json

NOTES
    This command is an internal implementation detail and may change or
    disappear without notice. This command is currently in ALPHA and may change
    without notice. Usually, users of ALPHA commands and flags need to apply
    for access, agree to applicable terms, and have their projects whitelisted.
    Contact Google or sign up on a product's page for ALPHA access. Product
    pages can be found at https://cloud.google.com/products/.

